<h1>DGrok Delphi Grammar</h1>
<p>DGrok is my project to write a parser for the Delphi
language, and then to build interesting tools on top of
that parser. For more information on DGrok, see the
<a href=3D"http://excastle.com/blog/category/2.aspx?Show=3DAll">
DGrok posts on my blog</a>.</p>
<p>This page shows the Delphi grammar as I've
<a href=3D"http://excastle.com/blog/archive/2007/08/28/48084.aspx">
puzzled it out</a> so far, and indicates how much of it
I've written a working parser for. Solid underline means
that rule is completely implemented in my parser; broken
underline means partly implemented; no underline means
something I haven't started yet.</p>
<p><b>Current status:</b> Completed 98 rules of 98 =3D 100% complete.</p>
<p>Last updated Wed Oct 03 22:48:00 Central Daylight Time 2007.</p>
<p>=97 <a href=3D"http://www.excastle.com/blog/">Joe White</a></p>
